CANADA DAYBOOK: RIM Reduces Profit Forecast; GDP Data Released

-- B y   D a v i d   S c a n l a n
-- 
2011-04-29T05:01:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/canada-daybook-rim-reduces-profit-forecast-gdp-data-released.html
Research In Motion Ltd. (RIM) , facing
intensifying competition from Apple Inc. and Google Inc., cut
its sales and profit forecasts for this quarter on slower-than-
expected demand for BlackBerry smartphones.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*As the election campaign heads into its final weekend, both
Prime Minister Stephen Harper and Liberal leader  Michael Ignatieff  will be stopping in key constituencies in Quebec and
Ontario, while New Democratic Party leader  Jack Layton  will be
in British Columbia.  ECONOMY: *Statistics Canada gives its report on February’s gross
domestic product. The data are forecast to show the expansion
stalled on a monthly basis, according to the median of 22
estimates in a Bloomberg survey.  EVENTS: *Insurance holding company Fairfax Financial Holdings
Ltd. is scheduled to hold a conference call to discuss first-
quarter financial results at 8:30 a.m. in Toronto.
*Agnico-Eagle Mines Ltd., a gold producer with operations in
Quebec, Mexico and Finland, is to hold a conference call to
discuss first-quarter earnings at 8:30 a.m. in Toronto.
*Centerra Gold Inc., which mines in Kyrgyzstan and Mongolia, is
to release first-quarter financial results after markets close.
* TransCanada Corp. (TRP) , Canada’s second-largest pipeline operator,
releases first-quarter results and holds its annual shareholder
meeting in Calgary.  MARKETS:
*The S&P/TSX rose 1.83 points to 13,894.40.
*Yields on two-year Government of Canada bonds fell 4 basis
points to 1.74 percent.
*The Canadian dollar fell 0.1 percent to 95.06 cents per  U.S.
dollar  at 4 p.m. yesterday in Toronto.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at   dscanlan@Bloomberg.net  